SIMPLE: lunule
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lunule
<hw>Lu"nule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>lunula</ets>, dim. of <ets>luna</ets> moon.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Anything crescent-shaped; a crescent-shaped part
or mark; a lunula; a lune.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A lune. See
<er>Lune</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A small or narrow
crescent.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A special area in front of the beak of
many bivalve shells. It sometimes has the shape of a double crescent,
but is oftener heart-shaped. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Bivalve</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lunulet</ent>⟦br⟧
